// Validator
// Validates diagram content as either SMACH YAML or Mermaid syntax.

SMACH YAML is detected first; if matched it uses a structural YAML validator.
Mermaid diagrams are validated by dynamically importing mermaid and calling parse().

FUNCTION isSmachYaml(content) -> boolean
  Return true if the content contains a smach_diagram: root key (regex check).

---

FUNCTION validateSmachYaml(content) -> ValidationResult
  Parse the YAML. Check for smach_diagram root, exactly one root StateMachine,
  valid type ('StateMachine'), at least one state, an initial_state, and at least one outcome.
  Return { valid: true } on success or { valid: false, error: message } on any failure.
  Catch YAML parse errors and return them as validation failures.

---

FUNCTION validate(content) -> ValidationResult
  CALLS: isSmachYaml (validator), validateSmachYaml (validator)
  Return invalid if content is empty.
  IF content looks like SMACH YAML, delegate to validateSmachYaml.
  ELSE dynamically import mermaid and call mermaid.parse().
  IF mermaid throws, extract a line number from the error message if available and return invalid.
  Return { valid: true } on success.
